Binding Assay: 6-week-old Sprague-Dawley (SD) rats were anesthetized in an ether container for 5 minutes, brains were separated from rats, and cortical regions were then separated from the brains of the rats. The cortical regions of the rats were put into a Tris-HCl buffer solution (50 mM, pH 7.4) and homogenized, and the homogenate was centrifuged twice at 4° C at a rotary speed of 50,000 g to obtain a precipitate (membrane protein). The precipitate was put into a buffer solution, and homogenized, which was used later as a protein source. 2 nM [3H]-8-OH-DPAT was used as a radioactive isotope, and 10 uM serotonin was used to remove non-specific bindings. 25 ul of the compound, 100 ul of an aqueous radioactive isotope solution, and 100 ul of the protein source were put together, and kept at 25° C. for 1 hour. The resulting mixture was filtered with a membrane filter in a 96-well harvester when the 96-well plate reaction was completed.

The precipitate was put into a buffer solution, and homogenized, which was used later as a protein source. 2 nM [3H]-8-OH-DPAT was used as a radioactive isotope, and 10 uM serotonin was used to remove non-specific bindings. 25 ul of the compound, 100 ul of an aqueous radioactive isotope solution, and 100 ul of the protein source were put together, and kept at 25° C. for 1 hour. The resulting mixture was filtered with a membrane filter in a 96-well harvester when the 96-well plate reaction was completed.

Binding Assay: 6-week-old Sprague-Dawley (SD) rats were anesthetized in an ether container for 5 minutes, brains were separated from rats, and cortical regions were then separated from the brains of the rats. The cortical regions of the rats were put into a Tris-HCl buffer solution (50 mM, pH 7.4) and homogenized, and the homogenate was centrifuged twice at 4° C at a rotary speed of 50,000 g to obtain a precipitate (membrane protein). The precipitate was put into a buffer solution, and homogenized, which was used later as a protein source. 2 nM [3H]-8-OH-DPAT was used as a radioactive isotope, and 10 uM serotonin was used to remove non-specific bindings. 25 ul of the compound, 100 ul of an aqueous radioactive isotope solution, and 100 ul of the protein source were put together, and kept at 25° C. for 1 hour. The resulting mixture was filtered with a membrane filter in a 96-well harvester when the 96-well plate reaction was completed.
